title: County Trail System, Westchester County New York, 2007
name: County Trail System, Westchester County New York, 2007
description:
"County Trailways System consisting of over 250 miles of existing and proposed trails and bicycle routes located within abandoned railroad rights of way, utility and parkway rights of way and transportation corridors. It is an extensive update to the previous coverage from 1996 and has been spatially adjusted to more accurately follow existing and proposed trail alignments based on 2004 digital aerial photography.  Updated as of June 2007.
The county trail system is based on the 2001 Tri-county trail master plan and also includes more recent trail alignments such as RiverWalk and the Colonial Greenway.  Also featured are trails such as: North and South County Trailways along the former Putnam ROW; Briarcliff-Peekskill Trailway; Bronx River Pathway; Old Croton Aqueduct Trailway; and East-West links such as the Tarrytown-Kensico Trailway. Road corridors proposed as bicycle "share the road" routes are also shown.  Not included are non-linear, self-contained, trail systems within county and other parks and open spaces."
